{;; Uniform Class/.member syntax is a stylistic migration with no
 ;; correctness gain, and the kernel stays babashka-compatible —
 ;; traditional interop reads fine in both runtimes.
 lint/prefer-method-values {:enabled false}
 ;; The flagged wrappers are EDN reader fns around static interop
 ;; (Instant/parse); bare method values are 1.12-only syntax and the
 ;; wrapper form is the one that reads identically under babashka.
 lint/fn-wrapper {:enabled false}
 ;; Catching Throwable is deliberate at our fail-well boundaries. The fuzz
 ;; harness feeds garbage and asserts the MANNER of failure, so it must
 ;; catch Errors (a recursion bomb raises StackOverflowError, not an
 ;; Exception); the top-level CLI net catches everything to print a bug
 ;; report instead of dumping a raw JVM stacktrace; the supervisor and the
 ;; I/O seams degrade on any Throwable rather than dying. Narrowing these to
 ;; Exception would silently let Errors through — the opposite of the
 ;; contract. See CLAUDE.md ("fail well: never a raw JVM exception").
 lint/catch-throwable {:enabled false}}
